  "texts": [
    "They are intuitive and interpretable, making them suitable for intrusion detection systems.",
    "Given a dataset with feature vectors X and corresponding binary labels y, where y represents normal (0) and anomalous (1) instances, Decision Trees aim to create a set of if-else rules to make predictions.",
    "A Decision Tree recursively splits the feature space into regions by selecting the feature and threshold that best separates the instances.",
    "The splitting process continues until a stopping criterion is met.",
    "The processed tree structure at the final step is a binary tree where the end nodes are the class predictions."
  ],
